tional Science Foundation via an Integrative Graduate Education and Research Traineeship  IGERT  grant  The grant provides two year IGERT fellowships to       Ph D  students over a five year period  as well as supporting a new curriculum and internship training for students  r n     The main components of the CTS program are course work  research projects  and development of the Intelligent Traveler Assistant  ITA  experimental prototype that demonstrates the research results  Some of the research projects and the prototype will be done in collaboration with our partners through internships   n r n            Our IGERT fellows are selected from Ph D  students in the following five core departments   Computer Science Urban Planning and Policy Civil and Materials Engineering Mechanical and Industrial Engineering Information and Decision Sciences Chicago Area Transportation Study the Chicago Transit Authority the Regional Transportation Authority Illinois Department of Transportation Argonne National Laboratory Motorola National University of Singapore INRIA Aalborg University 